@emilkowalski I'm just now coming across this feature, but this is a crucial feature in many of my apps. Would love to reopen if possible.

In one of my projects which uses [fkhadra/react-toastify](https://github.com/fkhadra/react-toastify), we use a default `ToastContainer` (toaster) at the app level that renders all toasts without a specified `containerId`, and we have another `ToastContainer` inside our Dialog component that renders toasts with its `containerId` in the corner of the dialog instead of the corner of the window/viewport.

So when using only one `ToastContainer`, you use this simple syntax:
```jsx
import { ToastContainer } from 'react-toastify';

function Main() {
  return (
    <>
      <ToastContainer />
      <OtherComponent />
    </>
  );
}

function OtherComponent() {
  return (
    <button onClick={() => toast("toast content")}>Trigger toast</button>
  );
}
```

When using more than one `ToastContainer`, you use the `enableMultiContainer` prop on every `ToastContainer` and apply an `id` to any you wish:
```jsx
import { ToastContainer } from 'react-toastify';

function Main() {
  return (
    <>
      <ToastContainer enableMultiContainer />
      <ToastContainer enableMultiContainer id="A" />
      <ToastContainer enableMultiContainer id="B" />
      <OtherComponent />
    </>
  );
}

function OtherComponent() {
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => toast("toast content")}>
        Trigger toast :: DEFAULT container
      </button>
      <button onClick={() => toast("toast content", { containerId: "A" })}>
        Trigger toast :: A container
      </button>
      <button onClick={() => toast("toast content", { containerId: "B" })}>
        Trigger toast :: B container
      </button>
    </>
  );
}
```

Check out these docs for more info:
* [ToastContainer](https://fkhadra.github.io/react-toastify/api/toast-container/)
* [Multi containers](https://fkhadra.github.io/react-toastify/multi-containers/)
* [toast](https://fkhadra.github.io/react-toastify/api/toast)
  ‚òùüèº this `toast` documentation might be worth perusing as inspiration for future updates

